busyIndicatorSize.!description: The size of the BusyIndicator. For controls with a width smaller 3rem a sap.ui.core.BusyIndicatorSize.Small should be used. If the size could vary in width and the width could get smaller than 3rem, the sap.ui.core.BusyIndicatorSize.Auto option could be used. The default is set to sap.ui.core.BusyIndicatorSize.Medium For a full screen BusyIndicator use sap.ui.core.BusyIndicatorSize.Large.

icon.!description:
Defines the icon to be displayed in the CustomSizeItem.
If no icon is specified, the default image is used, which is derived from the set width and height.

keepCropAspectRatio.!description: Defines whether aspect ratio should be kept when the crop area is expanded or shrunk in the CropRectangle or CropEllipse modes ({@link sap.suite.ui.commons.ImageEditorMode}).

mode.!description:
Image editor container mode.
Three modes are available: transform mode, crop mode, and filter mode (default).
The default mode provides filters for image editing: brightness, contrast, saturation, sepia grayscale, and others.

blocked.!description:
Deprecated! Since 1.69 The blocked property is deprecated. There is no accessibility support for this property. Blocked controls should not be used inside Controls, which rely on keyboard navigation, e.g. List controls.
Whether the control is currently in blocked state.

busyIndicatorDelay.!description: The delay in milliseconds, after which the busy indicator will show up for this control.

busy.!description: Whether the control is currently in busy state.

fieldGroupIds.!description: The IDs of a logical field group that this control belongs to. All fields in a logical field group should share the same fieldGroupId. Once a logical field group is left, the validateFieldGroup event is fired. For backward compatibility with older releases, field group IDs are syntactically not limited, but it is suggested to use only valid {@link sap.ui.core.ID}s. See {@link #attachValidateFieldGroup} or consult the {@link topic:5b0775397e394b1fb973fa207554003e Field Group} documentation.

height.!description:
* Defines the height of the CustomSizeItem.
This property is mandatory and must be greater than 0.

visible.!description: Whether the control should be visible on the screen. If set to false, a placeholder will be rendered to mark the location of the invisible control in the DOM of the current page. The placeholder will be hidden and have zero dimensions (display: none). Also see {@link module:sap/ui/core/InvisibleRenderer InvisibleRenderer}.

src.!description:
Image source.
Can be a file or Blob object, a URL address of the image, a Base64 data URL string, or any other source supported by the <img> HTML tag.

keepResizeAspectRatio.!description: Defines whether aspect ratio should be kept when the image is resized in the Resize mode ({@link sap.suite.ui.commons.ImageEditorMode}) or using the {@link #setWidth} or {@link #setHeight} methods.

customShapeSrc.!description:
Image source for the custom shape used in custom shape cropping.
Can be a file or Blob object, a URL address of the image, a Base64 data URL string, or any other source supported by the <img> HTML tag.
Note: In Internet Explorer, customShape doesn't support SVG files and will throw and exception if SVG files are used.

enabledButtons.!description: Controls order and availability of the buttons in the header panel of ImageEditorContainer.

width.!description:
Defines the width of the CustomSizeItem.
This property is mandatory and must be greater than 0.

scaleCropArea.!description:
Defines the behavior of the crop area when zooming in or out.
If set to true, the crop area is scaled up or down when the zoom level is changed.
If set to false, the crop area remains unchanged and keeps its size.

relative.!description:
Specifies whether the width and height properties use relative values (true) or absolute values (false).
When used in the customResizeItems aggregation of an {@link sap.suite.ui.commons.imageeditor.ImageEditorContainer}, width and height are multiplied by the width and height properties of the CustomSizeItem.
When used in the customRectangleCropItems or customEllipseCropItems aggregations of an {@link sap.suite.ui.commons.imageeditor.ImageEditorContainer}, aspect ratio is set to the width and height properties of the CustomSizeItem.

sap.suite.ui.commons.UnifiedThingInspect.!constructorDescription:
Constructor for a new UnifiedThingInspector. Accepts an object literal mSettings that defines initial property values, aggregated and associated objects as well as event handlers. See {@link sap.ui.base.ManagedObject#constructor} for a general description of the syntax of the settings object.

The supported settings are:

  • Properties
    • {@link #getHeight height} : sap.ui.core.CSSSize (default: 100%)
    • {@link #getTitle title} : string
    • {@link #getName name} : string
    • {@link #getDescription description} : string
    • {@link #getIcon icon} : sap.ui.core.URI
    • {@link #getTransactionsVisible transactionsVisible} : boolean (default: false)
    • {@link #getActionsVisible actionsVisible} : boolean (default: false)
    • {@link #getDestroyPageOnBack destroyPageOnBack} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getConfigurationVisible configurationVisible} : boolean (default: true)
  • Aggregations
    • {@link #getFacets facets} : sap.suite.ui.commons.FacetOverview[]
    • {@link #getFacetContent facetContent} : sap.ui.core.Control[]
    • {@link #getKpis kpis} : sap.suite.ui.commons.KpiTile[]
    • {@link #getTransactions transactions} : sap.ui.core.Control[]
    • {@link #getActions actions} : sap.m.Button[]
    • {@link #getPages pages} : sap.ui.core.Control[]
  • Events
    • {@link #event:backAction backAction} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:transactionsButtonPress transactionsButtonPress} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:actionsButtonPress actionsButtonPress} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:configurationButtonPress configurationButtonPress} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:navigate navigate} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:afterNavigate afterNavigate} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
In addition, all settings applicable to the base type {@link sap.ui.core.Control#constructor sap.ui.core.Control} can be used as well.

getWeight.!description:
Gets current value of property {@link #getWeight weight}. Weight of the group, relative to other groups in the status indicator. This property allows you to distribute the status indicator's value between groups of shapes that it contains. For example, for three groups with weights 10, 10, and 20 (total weight 40), the status indicator's value is distributed in the following way:
  • If the status indicator's value is below 25% (10 out of 40), the first group of shapes (weight 10) is partially filled, depending on the percentage value. For example, if the percentage value is 5, the first group of shapes is 1/5-full. The second and the third groups are empty.
  • If the status indicator's value is at least 25% but below 50%, the first group of shapes (weight 10) is filled, the second group (also weight 10) is partially filled, and the third group (weight 20) appears empty.
  • If the status indicator's value is at least 50% but below 100%, the first two groups of shapes (weight 10 each) are filled, but the third group (weight 20) is only partially filled.
  • If the status indicator's value is 100, all three groups of shapes are filled.
Default value is 10.

setWeight.!description:
Sets a new value for property {@link #getWeight weight}. Weight of the group, relative to other groups in the status indicator. This property allows you to distribute the status indicator's value between groups of shapes that it contains. For example, for three groups with weights 10, 10, and 20 (total weight 40), the status indicator's value is distributed in the following way:
  • If the status indicator's value is below 25% (10 out of 40), the first group of shapes (weight 10) is partially filled, depending on the percentage value. For example, if the percentage value is 5, the first group of shapes is 1/5-full. The second and the third groups are empty.
  • If the status indicator's value is at least 25% but below 50%, the first group of shapes (weight 10) is filled, the second group (also weight 10) is partially filled, and the third group (weight 20) appears empty.
  • If the status indicator's value is at least 50% but below 100%, the first two groups of shapes (weight 10 each) are filled, but the third group (weight 20) is only partially filled.
  • If the status indicator's value is 100, all three groups of shapes are filled.
When called with a value of null or undefined, the default value of the property will be restored. Default value is 10.

The supported settings are:

sap.suite.ui.commons.ThreePanelThingView.!helpDescription:
Deprecated! Since 1.32 Deprecated. Object page should be used instead.
This control extends the sap.ui.ux3.ThingViewer control. The first panel can display a thing icon, a title, the Action Menu button, up to two rows of text descriptions (the first is wrapped, the second is truncated), vertical navigation bar (sap.suite.ui.commons.VerticalNavigationBar), and an image aka key visual. The second panel displays the header area as a vertical panel containing ThingGroup objects. The third panel is a main content area designed to display ThingGroup objects.

getMenuContent.!description:
Gets content of aggregation {@link #getMenuContent menuContent}.

This aggregation allows you to add sap.ui.commons.Link items to the Action Menu. The menu appears as a popup when a user chooses a button in the top title section of the navigation panel.

removeAllMenuContent.!description:
Removes all the controls from the aggregation {@link #getMenuContent menuContent}.

Additionally, it unregisters them from the hosting UIArea.

setSidebarWidth.!description: Sets a new value for property {@link #getSidebarWidth sidebarWidth}. The width of the first panel that contains thing's title, icon, key visual and navigation bar. The default value is "244px". When called with a value of null or undefined, the default value of the property will be restored. Default value is 244px.

sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.Layout.!description: Types of layout algorithms that define the visual features and layout of the network graph.

SwimLanes.!description: Algorithm that arranges nodes into swim lanes, which are single-layer groups.

Forces.!description:
Algorithm that arranges the nodes freely in a force-directed manner, based on the attractive and repulsive forces within the graph.
This layout algorithm ignores node groups, so all nodes appear as standalone nodes not grouped in any way.

LayeredWithGroups.!description: Algorithm that arranges nodes into layers and ensures support for free-form groups.

TwoColumns.!description: Algorithm that supports nested groups, similar to SwimLanes, but arranges them into two columns only: one on the left and one on the right.

sap.suite.ui.commons.CalculationBuilderF.!description:
A custom function to be used in the calculation builder.
The default functions available for the calculation builder are defined in {@link sap.suite.ui.commons.CalculationBuilderFunctionType}.

getUseDefaultValidation.!description:
Gets current value of property {@link #getUseDefaultValidation useDefaultValidation}. Defines whether default validation should be used.
Set this property to false to provide your own validation algorithm using {@link sap.suite.ui.commons.CalculationBuilderValidationResult}.
If you do not provide your own validation algorithm for this custom function, set this property to true, and the function will be validated by the calculation builder. Default value is false.

getKey.!description:
Gets current value of property {@link #getKey key}. A key associated with the function. This property is mandatory.
The key is displayed in the text editor area of the calculation builder.

removeItem.!description: Removes a item from the aggregation {@link #getItems items}.

parameters.vItem: type: int|string|sap.suite.ui.commons.CalculationBuilderItem, description: The item to remove or its index or id

getMetadata.!description: Returns a metadata object for class sap.suite.ui.commons.CalculationBuilderFunction.

getLabel.!description:
Gets current value of property {@link #getLabel label}. Label for the function.
The label is displayed in the visual editor of the calculation builder and in the functions menu on the calculation builder's toolbar.

destroyItems.!description: Destroys all the items in the aggregation {@link #getItems items}.

setUseDefaultValidation.!description:
Sets a new value for property {@link #getUseDefaultValidation useDefaultValidation}. Defines whether default validation should be used.
Set this property to false to provide your own validation algorithm using {@link sap.suite.ui.commons.CalculationBuilderValidationResult}.
If you do not provide your own validation algorithm for this custom function, set this property to true, and the function will be validated by the calculation builder. When called with a value of null or undefined, the default value of the property will be restored. Default value is false.

parameters.bUseDefaultValidation: type: boolean, description: New value for property useDefaultValidation

setDescription.!description:
Sets a new value for property {@link #getDescription description}. Description of the function.
The description is displayed in the functions menu on the calculation builder's toolbar. If no description is specified, it is generated automatically based on the key property and the parameters defined in the items aggregation. When called with a value of null or undefined, the default value of the property will be restored.

parameters.sDescription: type: string, description: New value for property description

removeAllItems.!description:
Removes all the controls from the aggregation {@link #getItems items}.

Additionally, it unregisters them from the hosting UIArea.

getDescription.!description:
Gets current value of property {@link #getDescription description}. Description of the function.
The description is displayed in the functions menu on the calculation builder's toolbar. If no description is specified, it is generated automatically based on the key property and the parameters defined in the items aggregation.

extend.!description: Creates a new subclass of class sap.suite.ui.commons.CalculationBuilderFunction with name sClassName and enriches it with the information contained in oClassInfo. oClassInfo might contain the same kind of information as described in {@link sap.ui.core.Control.extend}.
extend.!type: fn(sClassName: String, oClassInfo?: Object, FNMetaImpl?: fn()) -> fn()

parameters.oClassInfo: type: object, description: Object literal with information about the class
parameters.FNMetaImpl: type: function, description: Constructor function for the metadata object; if not given, it defaults to the metadata implementation used by this class
parameters.sClassName: type: string, description: Name of the class being created

addItem.!description: Adds some item to the aggregation {@link #getItems items}.

parameters.oItem: type: sap.suite.ui.commons.CalculationBuilderItem, description: The item to add; if empty, nothing is inserted

getItems.!description:
Gets content of aggregation {@link #getItems items}. Holds the parameters that can be passed to the function.
For example, if the function has two parameters, the items aggregation may consist of:
  1. A {@link sap.suite.ui.commons.CalculationBuilderItem} with an empty key for the first argument entered by the user.
  2. A {@link sap.suite.ui.commons.CalculationBuilderItem} with a "," (comma) key for the comma that separates the arguments.
  3. A {@link sap.suite.ui.commons.CalculationBuilderItem} with an empty key for the second argument entered by the user.

sap.suite.ui.commons.CalculationBuilderF.!constructorDescription:
Constructor for a new custom function. Accepts an object literal mSettings that defines initial property values, aggregated and associated objects as well as event handlers. See {@link sap.ui.base.ManagedObject#constructor} for a general description of the syntax of the settings object.

The supported settings are:

  • Properties
    • {@link #getKey key} : string
    • {@link #getLabel label} : string
    • {@link #getDescription description} : string
    • {@link #getUseDefaultValidation useDefaultValidation} : boolean (default: false)
  • Aggregations
    • {@link #getItems items} : sap.suite.ui.commons.CalculationBuilderItem[]
In addition, all settings applicable to the base type {@link sap.ui.core.Control#constructor sap.ui.core.Control} can be used as well.

indexOfItem.!description: Checks for the provided sap.suite.ui.commons.CalculationBuilderItem in the aggregation {@link #getItems items}. and returns its index if found or -1 otherwise.

parameters.oItem: type: sap.suite.ui.commons.CalculationBuilderItem, description: The item whose index is looked for

A custom function to be used in the calculation builder.
The default functions available for the calculation builder are defined in {@link sap.suite.ui.commons.CalculationBuilderFunctionType}.

setLabel.!description:
Sets a new value for property {@link #getLabel label}. Label for the function.
The label is displayed in the visual editor of the calculation builder and in the functions menu on the calculation builder's toolbar. When called with a value of null or undefined, the default value of the property will be restored.

parameters.sLabel: type: string, description: New value for property label

insertItem.!description: Inserts a item into the aggregation {@link #getItems items}.

parameters.iIndex: type: int, description: The 0-based index the item should be inserted at; for a negative value of iIndex, the item is inserted at position 0; for a value greater than the current size of the aggregation, the item is inserted at the last position
parameters.oItem: type: sap.suite.ui.commons.CalculationBuilderItem, description: The item to insert; if empty, nothing is inserted

setKey.!description:
Sets a new value for property {@link #getKey key}. A key associated with the function. This property is mandatory.

parameters.sKey: type: string, description: New value for property key

borderColor.!description:
Border color.
The border color that is applied to elements in this custom status.

busyIndicatorSize.!description: The size of the BusyIndicator. For controls with a width smaller 3rem a sap.ui.core.BusyIndicatorSize.Small should be used. If the size could vary in width and the width could get smaller than 3rem, the sap.ui.core.BusyIndicatorSize.Auto option could be used. The default is set to sap.ui.core.BusyIndicatorSize.Medium For a full screen BusyIndicator use sap.ui.core.BusyIndicatorSize.Large.

titleLineSize.!description: Determines the maximum number of lines allowed for the node's label. If set to 0, the label may have an unlimited number of lines.

selectedBackgroundColor.!description:
Fill color when selected.
The fill color of a custom status element when you select it.

enableWheelZoom.!description: If this property is set to false, zooming in or out using the mouse wheel is available only when the Ctrl key is pressed.

busyIndicatorDelay.!description: The delay in milliseconds, after which the busy indicator will show up for this control.

lineType.!description: Defines the appearance of the line. Can be set to solid, dashed, or dotted.

iconSize.!description: Determines the size of the node's icon. This property can be applied only to circular nodes.

from.!description: Key of the node where the line begins.

legendColor.!description:
Color displayed in the graph's legend.
If not set, the fill color defined in the backgroundColor property is used.

borderStyle.!description: Style of the border. For {@link sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.Line} elements use this value as parameter for stroke-dasharray.

selected.!description: Shows if the node is selected. Once the node is selected, its appearance changes slightly to distinguish it from other nodes.

group.!description: Key of the group where this node is included.

maxWidth.!description: Maximum width allowed. The auto grow algorithm stops increasing the width at this value.

showDetailButton.!description: Determines if the details button is visible.

descriptionLineSize.!description: Determines the maximum number of lines allowed to be displayed in the node's description. If you want to hide the description, set this property to -1 (default). To display an unlimited number of lines, set this property to 0. This property does not affect the description that appears in the tooltip, which is always fully rendered.

visible.!description: Whether the control should be visible on the screen. If set to false, a placeholder will be rendered to mark the location of the invisible control in the DOM of the current page. The placeholder will be hidden and have zero dimensions (display: none). Also see {@link module:sap/ui/core/InvisibleRenderer InvisibleRenderer}.

shape.!description: Shape of the node. The shape is round by default. To create a rectangular node, set this property to Box.

labelStatus.!description: Name of custom status that can change the color of the label. Note that only contentColor, selectedContentColor and hoverContentColor are relevant to this attribute.

enableZoom.!description: If this property is set to false, zoom buttons are hidden, and the mouse wheel can be used for scrolling only.

headerCheckBoxState.!description: Defines if the Header checkbox should be displayed and whether it should be selected or not. By default, the checkbox is hidden. Available only for box nodes.

parentGroupKey.!description: Key of the parent group. Can be used only with the TwoColumns layout.

arrowOrientation.!description: Orientation of the line that defines the direction of the arrow.

coreNodeSize.!description:
Determines the size of a custom node, which can be useful for nodes that have text or other content outside of its shape.
This property is available for custom nodes only.

position.!description: Position of the action button. Available only for nodes.

status.!description: Status associated with this element. You can use any of the custom statuses defined by the statuses aggregation in the {@link sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.Graph} or use the default statuses provided by {@link sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.ElementStatus}.

selectedBorderColor.!description: Border color when selected. The border color of a custom status element when you select it.

backgroundImage.!description: An image to be rendered on the background.

collapsed.!description: Defines if the subtree of this node is collapsed. By default, it is expanded.

icon.!description: An icon associated with the element.

statusIcon.!description: An additional status icon displayed when the node is collapsed.

title.!description:
Title of the node.
The title that is applied to elements that are in this custom status. The title is displayed in the legend.

valueStatus.!description: Name of custom status that can change the color of the value. Note that only contentColor, selectedContentColor and hoverContentColor are relevant to this attribute.

enabled.!description: Indicates whether the action button is enabled.

showActionLinksButton.!description: Determines if the links button is visible.

showExpandButton.!description: Determines if the expand button is visible.

blocked.!description:
Deprecated! Since 1.69 The blocked property is deprecated. There is no accessibility support for this property. Blocked controls should not be used inside Controls, which rely on keyboard navigation, e.g. List controls.
Whether the control is currently in blocked state.

borderWidth.!description: Border width of the element in specific units (for example 2px).

busy.!description: Whether the control is currently in busy state.

hoverBorderColor.!description:
Border color on hover.
The border color of a custom status element when you hover over it.

hoverContentColor.!description: Content color on hover. Color of the content (text or icon) inside the custom status element when you hover over it.

fieldGroupIds.!description: The IDs of a logical field group that this control belongs to. All fields in a logical field group should share the same fieldGroupId. Once a logical field group is left, the validateFieldGroup event is fired. For backward compatibility with older releases, field group IDs are syntactically not limited, but it is suggested to use only valid {@link sap.ui.core.ID}s. See {@link #attachValidateFieldGroup} or consult the {@link topic:5b0775397e394b1fb973fa207554003e Field Group} documentation.

hoverBackgroundColor.!description:
Fill color on hover.
The fill color of a custom status element, line, or group when you hover over it.

renderType.!description: Nodes rendering type. For optimal performance and usability, it is recommended that you use HTML whenever possible.

directRenderNodeLimit.!description: This property affects the threshold at which the renderer switches from link rendering to direct graph rendering. Rendering using xlink is much faster, but with larger graphs it may slow down the browser performance. Modify this property with care. Please also keep in mind that a graph map that is rendered directly does not adapt to changes until it's fully rerendered. Available only for SVG rendering type.

useFocusColorAsContentColor.!description:
Defines whether the focus border should match the color of the content in focus. If false, the focus border has the default color.
This property can be used only for nodes and groups of nodes.

value.!description: Value of the attribute. If set to null, the value is not displayed.

orientation.!description: Orientation of the graph flow. This property is used by layout algorithms.

backgroundColor.!description:
Fill color.
The fill color that is applied to elements and lines that are in this custom status.

src.!description: Relative or absolute path to the image file.

minWidth.!description:
Minimal width of the group (swim lane) for the SwimLanes type of {@link sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.LayoutRenderType}.
If not specified, the width of the group (swim lane) is defined automatically, based on the width of the nodes included in the swim lane.
If the width specified in this property is too small to fit the nodes included in this group (swim lane), the width is increased accordingly.

label.!description: Label of the attribute. If set to null, the label is not displayed.

contentColor.!description:
Color of the content (text or icon) inside the node.
The color is applied to a node's content when it enters this custom status.

noDataText.!description:
Text displayed when no data is set.
This property takes effect only when the noData property is set to true.

selectedContentColor.!description: Content color when selected. Color of the content (text or icon) inside the custom status node when you select it.

stretchToCenter.!description:
Extends the line up to the node's horizontal or vertical axis to ensure that it meets the shape's outline even when a fancy shape is used.
Available for custom nodes only.

x.!description:
The x coordinate of the node. This value must be set after the layout algorithm has finished arranging the graph. It may come from the input data but is not required for most layout algorithms.
Works only for CustomLayout or NoopLayout layout algorithms. Other layout algorithms override this property. However, you can still change it using an afterLayouting event.

headerContentColor.!description:
Color of the header content (title and icon) of the node.
Applicable only to the rectangular nodes.

y.!description:
The y coordinate of the node. This value must be set after the layout algorithm has finished arranging the graph. It may come from the input data but is not required for most layout algorithms.
Works only for CustomLayout or NoopLayout layout algorithms. Other layout algorithms override this property. However, you can still change it using an afterLayouting event.

noData.!description:
Set this property to true if you want to notify the user that no data has been loaded.
There is no internal check for data received, so we recommend that you make sure you set it correctly when there is no data received, not just when the application is waiting for data to be retrieved.

to.!description: Key of the node the line leads to.

arrowPosition.!description: Position of the arrow on the line. Can be set to End, Middle, or Start.

sap.suite.ui.commons.RepeaterViewConfigu.!constructorDescription:
Constructor for a new RepeaterViewConfiguration. Accepts an object literal mSettings that defines initial property values, aggregated and associated objects as well as event handlers. See {@link sap.ui.base.ManagedObject#constructor} for a general description of the syntax of the settings object.

The supported settings are:

  • Properties
    • {@link #getTitle title} : string
    • {@link #getIcon icon} : sap.ui.core.URI
    • {@link #getIconHovered iconHovered} : sap.ui.core.URI
    • {@link #getPath path} : string
    • {@link #getItemMinWidth itemMinWidth} : int (default: -1)
    • {@link #getNumberOfTiles numberOfTiles} : int (default: -1)
    • {@link #getResponsive responsive} : any (default: false)
    • {@link #getExternal external} : boolean (default: false)
    • {@link #getIconSelected iconSelected} : sap.ui.core.URI
    • {@link #getItemHeight itemHeight} : int
  • Aggregations
    • {@link #getTemplate template} : sap.ui.core.Control
    • {@link #getExternalRepresentation externalRepresentation} : sap.ui.core.Control
In addition, all settings applicable to the base type {@link sap.ui.core.Control#constructor sap.ui.core.Control} can be used as well.

getTitle.!description:
Gets current value of property {@link #getTitle title}.

The title of the view to be displayed in sap.suite.ui.commons.ViewRepeater view selector. If neither this nor "icon" property are defined, the default title "View ##" will be shown, where ## is an index number of the view in View Repeater starting from 1.

setIconHovered.!description: Sets a new value for property {@link #getIconHovered iconHovered}. A path to the icon representing this view in sap.suite.ui.commons.ViewRepeater view selector when the regular icon is hovered. When called with a value of null or undefined, the default value of the property will be restored.

parameters.sIconHovered: type: sap.ui.core.URI, description: New value for property iconHovered

getPath.!description:
Gets current value of property {@link #getPath path}.

A path used for rows/titles data binding.

getItemMinWidth.!description: Gets current value of property {@link #getItemMinWidth itemMinWidth}. The minimal width of the tile in this view. Only applicable if "responsive" property is set to true. Default value is -1.

parameters.oExternalRepresentation: type: sap.ui.core.Control, description: The externalRepresentation to set

destroyExternalRepresentation.!description: Destroys the externalRepresentation in the aggregation {@link #getExternalRepresentation externalRepresentation}.

setItemHeight.!description: Sets a new value for property {@link #getItemHeight itemHeight}. The height of the tile in this view in pixels. Only applicable if the responsive property is set to true. This value is used for calculating the number of tile rows. When called with a value of null or undefined, the default value of the property will be restored.

parameters.iItemHeight: type: int, description: New value for property itemHeight

setResponsive.!description: Sets a new value for property {@link #getResponsive responsive}. This parameter indicates whether the content is shown in rows or tiles. If false, the content is shown in rows just like in core sap.ui.commons.RowRepeater. If true, the content is shown in tiles (similar to sap.ui.ux3.DataSet control) that have minimal width defined by the "itemMinWidth" property. The number of columns depends on the parent control's width. If you resize the control, the number of columns may change respectively so that the content tiles can fill the entire space of a row. When called with a value of null or undefined, the default value of the property will be restored. Default value is false.

parameters.oResponsive: type: any, description: New value for property responsive

setIconSelected.!description: Sets a new value for property {@link #getIconSelected iconSelected}. A path to the icon representing this view in sap.suite.ui.commons.ViewRepeater view selector when the regular icon is selected. When called with a value of null or undefined, the default value of the property will be restored.

parameters.sIconSelected: type: sap.ui.core.URI, description: New value for property iconSelected

sap.suite.ui.commons.NoteTakerFeeder.!constructorDescription:
Constructor for a new NoteTakerFeeder. Accepts an object literal mSettings that defines initial property values, aggregated and associated objects as well as event handlers. See {@link sap.ui.base.ManagedObject#constructor} for a general description of the syntax of the settings object.

The supported settings are:

  • Properties
    • {@link #getBody body} : string
    • {@link #getTitle title} : string
    • {@link #getTags tags} : object (default: [])
    • {@link #getThumbUp thumbUp} : boolean
    • {@link #getThumbDown thumbDown} : boolean
    • {@link #getAttachmentUploadUrl attachmentUploadUrl} : string
    • {@link #getAttachmentName attachmentName} : string (default: attachment)
  • Aggregations
  • Events
    • {@link #event:addNote addNote} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:attachmentSelect attachmentSelect} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:attachmentUploadComplete attachmentUploadComplete} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:attachmentDelete attachmentDelete} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:attachmentClick attachmentClick} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
In addition, all settings applicable to the base type {@link sap.ui.core.Control#constructor sap.ui.core.Control} can be used as well.

sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.Graph.!constructorDescription:
Constructor for a new Graph. Accepts an object literal mSettings that defines initial property values, aggregated and associated objects as well as event handlers. See {@link sap.ui.base.ManagedObject#constructor} for a general description of the syntax of the settings object.

The supported settings are:

  • Properties
    • {@link #getHeight height} : sap.ui.core.CSSSize (default: 100%)
    • {@link #getWidth width} : sap.ui.core.CSSSize (default: 100%)
    • {@link #getOrientation orientation} : sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.Orientation (default: LeftRight)
    • {@link #getEnableZoom enableZoom} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getEnableWheelZoom enableWheelZoom} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getBackgroundImage backgroundImage} : sap.ui.core.URI
    • {@link #getBackgroundColor backgroundColor} : sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.BackgroundColor (default: White)
    • {@link #getRenderType renderType} : sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.RenderType (default: Html)
    • {@link #getNoData noData} : boolean (default: false)
    • {@link #getNoDataText noDataText} : string (default: )
  • Aggregations
    • {@link #getLines lines} : sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.Line[]
    • {@link #getNodes nodes} : sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.Node[]
    • {@link #getGroups groups} : sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.Group[]
    • {@link #getLegend legend} : sap.ui.core.Control
    • {@link #getLayoutAlgorithm layoutAlgorithm} : sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.layout.LayoutAlgorithm
    • {@link #getStatuses statuses} : sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.Status[]
  • Associations
    • {@link #getAriaDescribedBy ariaDescribedBy} : (sap.ui.core.ID | sap.ui.core.Control)[]
    • {@link #getAriaLabelledBy ariaLabelledBy} : (sap.ui.core.ID | sap.ui.core.Control)[]
  • Events
    • {@link #event:graphReady graphReady} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:afterLayouting afterLayouting} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:beforeLayouting beforeLayouting} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:zoomChanged zoomChanged} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:failure failure} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:selectionChange selectionChange} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:searchSuggest searchSuggest} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:search search} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
In addition, all settings applicable to the base type {@link sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.SvgBase#constructor sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.SvgBase} can be used as well.

sap.suite.ui.commons.GenericTile2X2.!constructorDescription:
Constructor for a new GenericTile2X2. Accepts an object literal mSettings that defines initial property values, aggregated and associated objects as well as event handlers. See {@link sap.ui.base.ManagedObject#constructor} for a general description of the syntax of the settings object.

The supported settings are:

  • Properties
    • {@link #getHeader header} : string
    • {@link #getSubheader subheader} : string
    • {@link #getFailedText failedText} : string
    • {@link #getSize size} : sap.suite.ui.commons.InfoTileSize (default: Auto)
    • {@link #getBackgroundImage backgroundImage} : sap.ui.core.URI
    • {@link #getHeaderImage headerImage} : sap.ui.core.URI
    • {@link #getFrameType frameType} : sap.suite.ui.commons.FrameType (default: OneByOne)
    • {@link #getState state} : sap.suite.ui.commons.LoadState (default: Loaded)
    • {@link #getImageDescription imageDescription} : string
  • Aggregations
    • {@link #getTileContent tileContent} : sap.suite.ui.commons.TileContent2X2[]
    • {@link #getIcon icon} : sap.ui.core.Control
  • Events
    • {@link #event:press press} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
In addition, all settings applicable to the base type {@link sap.ui.core.Control#constructor sap.ui.core.Control} can be used as well.

setSize.!description: Sets a new value for property {@link #getSize size}. The size of the tile. If not set, then the default size is applied based on the device tile. When called with a value of null or undefined, the default value of the property will be restored. Default value is Auto.

parameters.sSize: type: sap.suite.ui.commons.InfoTileSize, description: New value for property size

Gets current value of property {@link #getImageDescription imageDescription}.

Description of a header image that is used in the tooltip.

parameters.sFailedText: type: string, description: New value for property failedText

setHeaderImage.!description: Sets a new value for property {@link #getHeaderImage headerImage}. The image to be displayed as a graphical element within the header. This can be an image or an icon from the icon font. When called with a value of null or undefined, the default value of the property will be restored.

parameters.sHeaderImage: type: sap.ui.core.URI, description: New value for property headerImage

Removes all the controls from the aggregation {@link #getTileContent tileContent}.

Additionally, it unregisters them from the hosting UIArea.

attachPress.!description: Attaches event handler fnFunction to the {@link #event:press press} event of this sap.suite.ui.commons.GenericTile2X2. When called, the context of the event handler (its this) will be bound to oListener if specified, otherwise it will be bound to this sap.suite.ui.commons.GenericTile2X2 itself. The event is fired when the user chooses the tile.
attachPress.!type: fn(oData?: Object, fnFunction: fn(), oListener?: Object) -> sap.suite.ui.commons.GenericTile2X2

parameters.fnFunction: type: function, description: The function to be called when the event occurs
parameters.oData: type: object, description: An application-specific payload object that will be passed to the event handler along with the event object when firing the event
