isTitleClickable.!description:
Deprecated! Since 1.26 According to the new requirement there should be only one click event for each node (click on the whole node – see Press event) that is why titlePress event should not be used any longer. Hence isTitleClickable should not be used either.
Specifies if the node title is clickable.

allowLogicalOperators.!description: Defines whether logical operators (AND, OR, XOR, NOT) are allowed.

favoriteActionEnabled.!description: Favorite action enabled/disabled. If disabled the action will be invisible.

flagActionEnabled.!description: Flag action enabled/disabled. If disabled the action will be invisible.

fullScreen.!description: Display the chart and the toolbar in full screen or normal mode.

tags.!description: The list of tags selected for addition to a new note card.

size.!description: Updates the size of the tile. If not set then the default size is applied based on the device tile.

wrapLabels.!description: Set to true to wrap text labels in the dialog that opens when the user clicks or taps the 'Details' button.

showItemFilter.!description: Show item filter in filter area.

placement.!description: The ActionSheet behaves as an sap.m.Popover in iPad and this property is the information about on which side will the popover be placed at. Possible values are sap.m.PlacementType.Left, sap.m.PlacementType.Right, sap.m.PlacementType.Top, sap.m.PlacementType.Bottom, sap.m.PlacementType.Horizontal, sap.m.PlacementType.HorizontalPreferedLeft, sap.m.PlacementType.HorizontalPreferedRight, sap.m.PlacementType.Vertical, sap.m.PlacementType.VerticalPreferedTop, sap.m.PlacementType.VerticalPreferedBottom. The default value is sap.m.PlacementType.Bottom.

iconPath.!description: A path to the BusinessCard icon.

showFullScreen.!description: Set to true to display the full screen icon. Set to false to hide it.

firstTitle.!description: First Line of the Thing Inspector Title

growingThreshold.!description: Number of posts requested from the server at a time. Each time when the timeline needs to load more posts, it will request exactly this amount. The number of posts displayed in the timeline is increased by this number. If set to 0, all posts are fetched and displayed on the initial load.

icon.!description: The icon to be displayed as a graphical element within the header. This can be an image or an icon from the icon font.

smallStepWidth.!description: The grip can only be moved in steps of this width.

valueColor.!description: The semantic color of the value.

uid.!description: The card ID. This property should be set by an application developer.

publicationDate.!description: The date the feed item was published.

highlighted.!description: The parameter defines if the node should be displayed in highlighted state.

showTopLabels.!description: If this property is set to false, both top labels are hidden.

toplevelVariant.!description: Defines whether the navigation bar shall have top-level appearance

displayValue1.!description: If this property is set, it is rendered instead of value1.

displayValue2.!description: If this property is set, it is rendered instead of value2.

x.!description: X value for the given point.

showDividers.!description: If set to true, shows dividers between scrollable items.

y.!description: Y value for the given point.

currentPage.!description: The index of the page currently displayed. The index starts at 1.

displayTime.!description: The time of the slide display in milliseconds.

showLegend.!description: Set to true to display the charts' legends. Set to false to hide them. See also showLegendButton.

showValueMarker.!description: If set to true, shows the value marker.

showLabel.!description: Determines if the labels are displayed or not.

allowStringConstants.!description:
Defines whether string constants are allowed.
If set to true, the calculation builder doesn't validate custom strings as errors.

pinGrip.!description: Property to pin Grip (left grip) of the slider so that user cannot move it with key or mouse clicks.

defaultImages.!description: A list of default images that is cycled by the control when no image is available for a feed item or when no feed items exist. After a random image is displayed first time, control cycles through this list of images.

lite.!description: The split button is rendered as lite split button.

image.!description: The image associated with the feed item.

thumbDown.!description: Sets negative indication for a new note.

showActualValue.!description: If set to true, shows the numeric actual value. This property works in Actual mode only.

titleAbbreviation.!description: Title abbreviation is used in zoom level 'Three'.

iconTooltip.!description: Tooltip for an icon displayed on the timeline axis.

enableScroll.!description: If set to true, the Timeline control has its own scroll bar, with the scrolling taking place within the Timeline control itself. Scrolling is required if you want to enable the lazyLoading property.

viewAllTrigger.!description: The View All link appears in the Note Taker card if a body text length exceeds the specified value.

external.!description: Indicates if the external representation of the current view is rendered.

fractionLabel.!description: The fraction label. If this property is specified, it is displayed instead of the label that is based on the fraction property.

alignment.!description: Defines the alignment of timeline posts relative to the timeline axis. This option can be used for single-sided timelines only. If the axisOrientation property is set to Horizontal, the Right value is interpreted as bottom alignment and the Left value as top alignment.

iconDensityAware.!description:
By default, this is set to true but then one or more requests are sent trying to get the density perfect version of image if this version of image doesn't exist on the server.

If only one version of image is provided, set this value to false to avoid the attempt of fetching density perfect image.

valueUnit.!description: The percent sign, currency symbol, or unit for a value.

scrollStep.!description: Number of pixels to scroll when the user chooses Next or Previous buttons. Relevant only for desktop.

maxYValue.!description: If this property is set it indicates the value X axis ends with.

scope.!description: Changes the visualization in order to enable additional actions with the Generic Tile.

fieldGroupIds.!description: The IDs of a logical field group that this control belongs to. All fields in a logical field group should share the same fieldGroupId. Once a logical field group is left, the validateFieldGroup event is fired. For backward compatibility with older releases, field group IDs are syntactically not limited, but it is suggested to use only valid {@link sap.ui.core.ID}s. See {@link #attachValidateFieldGroup} or consult the {@link topic:5b0775397e394b1fb973fa207554003e Field Group} documentation.

isFiltered.!description: Shows whether the note card is hidden by the applied filter.

useIconTooltip.!description: Decides whether a default Icon tooltip should be used if no tooltip is set.

actualValueLabel.!description: If set, displays a specified label instead of the numeric actual value.

showHeader.!description: Shows or hides a middle panel named Header that contains general information.

length.!description: The number of the retrieved entries for the cloud of the links in the quadrant. The quadrant can display fewer links than retrieved. The font size of the links in the quadrant depends on the measure number. The font size of the links is relative in the retrieved group.

counter.!description: Defines the counter value of the list items.

enableBackendFilter.!description:
Deprecated! Since 1.46.0 Use the enableModelFilter property instead.
Enables fetching data from backend instead of deriving filter values from the frontend values (displayed list). As of version 1.46, replaced by {@link sap.suite.ui.commons.Timeline#getEnableModelFilter}.

userName.!description: User name shown in the post title.

showLabels.!description: Defines if the connection labels are shown or not.

allTags.!description: Contains an array of the String type tags available for selection during the card update.

showTimeFilter.!description: Shows the time range filter in the filter menu.

busyIndicatorSize.!description: The size of the BusyIndicator. For controls with a width smaller 3rem a sap.ui.core.BusyIndicatorSize.Small should be used. If the size could vary in width and the width could get smaller than 3rem, the sap.ui.core.BusyIndicatorSize.Auto option could be used. The default is set to sap.ui.core.BusyIndicatorSize.Medium For a full screen BusyIndicator use sap.ui.core.BusyIndicatorSize.Large.

text.!description: Text shown inside the timeline post.

scaleColor.!description: The background color of the scale. The theming is enabled only for the default value of this property.

userPicture.!description: Picture shown next to the user name.

totalScale.!description: The scaling factor that is displayed next to the total value.

axisOrientation.!description: Defines the orientation of the timeline. Can be set to Vertical or Horizontal.

status.!description:
Indicates the post status. The status affects the post's icon color. Supported values:
  • Information
  • Success
  • Warning
  • Error

dateTime.!description:
Date and time value of the timeline post. This value must be in one of the following formats:
  • A valid instance of the Date object.
  • An integer representing Unix time (also known as POSIX or Epoch time) in milliseconds.
  • A string with an integer representing Unix time in milliseconds.
  • A string that contains Date([number]), where [number] represents Unix time in milliseconds.
If this property has any other format, the timeline will try to parse it using Date.parse. It is not recommended to use this functionality, as different web browsers implement this function differently, which may lead to unpredictable behavior.

numberOfTiles.!description: The number of tiles/rows that will be shown on a single page in this view.

overflowItemsToUpperCase.!description: Sets the appearance of the menu items in the overflow menu to uppercase

transitionTime.!description: The time of the slide changing in milliseconds.

activeIcon.!description: The source property of an alternative icon for the active (depressed) state of the button. Both active and default icon properties should be defined and have the same type: image or icon font. If the icon property is not set or has a different type, the active icon is not displayed.

targetValue.!description: The target value that is displayed as a black vertical bar.

describedBy.!description: Identifies one or more elements that describe the object. See the related labelledBy property.

minYValue.!description: If this property is set it indicates the value X axis ends with.

max.!description: Maximal value of the slider Note: If min is larger than max both values will be switched

footerColor.!description: The semantic color of the footer.

showSeparator.!description: Defines whether a connector line should be displayed between this node and the node that follows it.

secondTitle.!description: Second Line of the Thing Inspector Title

targetValueLabel.!description: If set, displays a specified label instead of the numeric target value.

itemHeight.!description: The height of the tile in the current view in pixels. Only applicable if the responsive property is set to true. This value is used for calculating the number of tile rows.

body.!description: The text inside the note card.

logo.!description: A URL of the source of an image known as key visual. This can be a company logo or other essential graphics.

imageTooltip.!description: A tooltip that is set for an image.

selected.!description: The parameter defines if the node should be displayed in selected state.

drawData.!description: This is an array of the following attributes for one element: 1. flowLine (string) - A connection definition where the line should be drawn. A string which defines a course of a flow line. A flow line is a connection between nodes in a process flow control. The string can contain the following characters: - "r" for right, - "t" for top, - "l" for left, - "b" for bottom. 2. targetNodeState (ProcessFlowNodeState) - A copy of the target node status. If the target node is created, the line is solid. If the target node is planned, the line is dashed. 3. displayState (ProcessFlowDisplayState) - Display state of the node. This property defines if the node is displayed regularly, highlighted, or dimmed in combination with a selected visual style of the control. 4. hasArrow (boolean) - Indicates if the line has an arrow on the right end.

maxValue.!description: The maximum scale value for the chart used to define the value range of the scale for comparing different values.

shrinkable.!description: If it is set to true, the height of the control is defined by its content.

sort.!description: Indicates whether the data should be sorted. If set to false the data model's default sorting is applied.

configurationVisible.!description: If set to true, the Configuration button appears.

unit.!description: The percent sign, the currency symbol, or the unit of measure.

itemMinWidth.!description: The minimal width of the tile for the current view. Only applicable if "responsive" property is set to true.

heigth.!description:
Deprecated! Since 1.20.2 Wrong property name
Height of the HeaderCell control.

focused.!description: The parameter defines if the node should be displayed in focus state.

header.!description: Stores the Note Taker card header.

position.!description: Position of the lane in the process flow control. Numbering of the position has to be sequential and needs to start from 0.

hasPopup.!description: Indicates that the element has a popup context menu or a submenu.

footer.!description: The footer text of the tile.

backgroundImage.!description: The URI of the background image.

formattedLabel.!description:
If set to true, the fractionLabel property is used instead of the combination of the fraction value and scaling factor.
The default value is false, which means that the fraction value, defined by the fraction property, and the scaling factor, defined by the fractionScale property are displayed separately.

enableBusyIndicator.!description: When this property is set to true, the timeline displays a busy indicator when loading data. This busy indicator blocks the interaction with the items until the data loading is complete. It is strongly recommended to use this option. Loading data without a busy indicator may confuse the users.

navigated.!description: The navigated state of the list item. If set to true, a navigation indicator is displayed at the end of the list item.

showCancelButton.!description: If this is set to true, there will be a cancel button shown below the action buttons. There won't be any cancel button shown in iPad regardless of this property. The default value is set to true.

isResponsive.!description:
Deprecated! Since 1.60 undefined
If this set to true, width and height of the control are determined by the width and height of the container in which the control is placed or by the width and height property.

total.!description: The total value. The total value is represented by a full circle, or 360 degrees value on the chart.

heightType.!description: Indicates the height of the control in the predifened values. If set to None, then the height is defined by the depricated height property.

destroyPageOnBack.!description: If set to true, destroys a page when the user chooses the Back button to leave this page.

disabledDefaultTokens.!description:
Default operators or functions that are disabled. Delimiter for multiple items is ';'.
Example of usage: +;-;sqrt

busy.!description: Whether the control is currently in busy state.

design.!description: The visual design of the control.

layoutType.!description:
Defines the layout type used for the calculation builder.
The layout may include a visual editor, a text editor, or both. In addition, you can set the text editor to be read-only.

editable.!description: Using the slider interactively requires value "true".

stepWidth.!description:
Distance between this node and the following node.
When set to a percentage value, the distance is calculated based on the height of the parent container.

deltaValueLabel.!description: If set, displays a specified label instead of the calculated numeric delta value.

laneId.!description: Specifies the assignment of the node to the respective lane.

enableSocial.!description: Adds a Reply link to the posts on a social timeline that allows users to reply to posts. When a user adds a reply, an event is fired. This event should be handled by external code.

replyCount.!description: Number of replies to a timeline post.

showSort.!description: Show sort icon in the header bar. For displaying this icon, sorting have to be allowed.

attachmentName.!description: The attachment property name for identification on the server side after sending data to the server.

showSelectionDetails.!description: Set to true to display the 'Details' button that opens a popup dialog with details about the selected data from the VizFrame based chart.

zoomLevel.!description: Current zoom level for the lane header.

value2.!description: The second value for delta calculation.

value1.!description: The first value for delta calculation.

showLegendButton.!description: Set to true or false to display or hide a button for controlling the visbility of the chart's legend. Please be aware that setting this property to true indirectly is setting showLegend to false. If you need to hide the button but to show the legend, you need to set showLegend at a later point in time (onBeforeRendering). The execution order of the combined properties is not guaranteed by the control.

styled.!description: Indicatied if the button is styled. If not it is rendered as native HTML-button. In this case a custom styling can be added usig addStyleClass.

allowComparisonOperators.!description: Defines whether comparison operators (<, >, <=, >=, =, !=) are allowed.

useDefaultValidation.!description:
Defines whether default validation should be used.
Set this property to false to provide your own validation algorithm using {@link sap.suite.ui.commons.CalculationBuilderValidationResult}.
If you do not provide your own validation algorithm for this custom function, set this property to true, and the function will be validated by the calculation builder.

iconFirst.!description: If set to true (default), the display sequence is 1. icon 2. control text .

minHeight.!description: The minimal height of the control.

busyIndicatorDelay.!description: The delay in milliseconds, after which the busy indicator will show up for this control.

openButtonVisible.!description: Defines whether the 'Open' button shall be visible.

height.!description: The height of the control. Only applicable if the responsive property is set to true.

showFractions.!description: If set to true, the fraction values are displayed next to the chart. The default setting is true.

showIntermediary.!description:
Defines whether an object should be displayed between this node and the following node.
When set to true, a vertical red bar is displayed by default. To define custom objects, use the intermediary aggregation.

maxXValue.!description: If this property is set, it indicates the value the X-axis ends with.

readOnly.!description: Defines whether the control is read-only.

forecastValue.!description: The forecast value that is displayed in Actual mode only. If set, the forecast value bar appears in the background of the actual value bar.

showPersonalization.!description: Set to true to display the personalization icon. Set to false to hide it.

stepLabels.!description: Display step numbers for the ticks on the slider.

forceGrowing.!description: If set to true, the Show More button is displayed when the user scrolls along the timeline axis.

labels.!description: Labels to be displayed instead of numbers. Attribute totalUnits and label count should be the same Note: To show the labels stepLabels must be activated.

dateTimePath.!description: Path for dateTime in mode binding. Use this property when you use factory function for TimeLineItem creation. When every item has different path or the datetime is calculated in factory sorting, filtering and searching has to be done manually using events. If not set for factory binding filter and sorting won't work.

unread.!description: Activates the unread indicator for the list item, if set to true. Note: This flag is ignored when the showUnread property of the parent is set to false.

updateActionEnabled.!description: Update action enabled/disabled. If disabled the action will be invisible.

minXValue.!description: If this property is set it indicates the value X axis ends with.

groupBy.!description: Groups the timeline posts by a field. Only fields that contain date values are supported.

pinGrip2.!description: Property to pin Grip2 (right grip) of the slider so that user cannot move it with key or mouse clicks.

min.!description: Minimal value of the slider. Note: If min is larger than max both values will be switched

iconSelected.!description: A path to the icon representing this view in sap.suite.ui.commons.ViewRepeater view selector when the regular icon is selected.

key.!description: A key for a filter criterion. Each filter criterion must have a unique key.

scrollable.!description:
By default, the control body is embedded into a scroll container of fixed size, so the user can put the control into a fixed size layout. When the control body (the graph) gets larger, the container cuts the overflowing parts of the graph and the cut parts can be displayed by scrolling the control body. When the control body fits into the container limits, obviously no scrolling is possible (and makes sense).

The scrolling feature can be turned off by setting this property value to false, so the width/height of the whole control will change as the flow graph gets smaller/larger. In this case the control body could not be scrolled, as the control body size matches the control container size.

timestamp.!description: Stores a timestamp of the Note Taker card.

expression.!description:
Holds the arithmetic expression.
Use either this property or aggregation Items. Not both.

transactionsVisible.!description: If set to true, the Transaction button appears.

sortOldestFirst.!description: Whether the oldest item will be displayed first.

displayValue.!description: If this property is set then it will be displayed instead of value.

textHeight.!description:
Height of the timeline posts. It can be set to either of the following types of values:
  • Automatic – If set to automatic, the optimal post height is calculated automatically to fit the timeline height specified by the height parameter. This option works only in horizontal timelines and only when the timeline height is defined. In vertical timelines, this setting is ignored.
  • Number – If set to a number, a corresponding number of text lines is displayed in every post.
  • Pixels – If set to a number followed by px, such as 50px, the closest number in lines is calculated and applied to the timeline posts, so that the post height corresponds to the specified number of pixels and the text lines are not cut off in the middle of a line.
  • Any other valid {@link sap.ui.core.CSSSize CSSSize} value that is inserted into the text wrapper without being changed.

displayDuration.!description: The length of time in seconds the control displays each feed item. Default value is 5 seconds.

enableDoubleSided.!description: If set to true, timeline posts are displayed on both sides of the timeline axis.

texts.!description: The property contains the additional texts on the node. The expected type is array of strings. One array must not contain more than two strings. Additional strings in the array will be ignored.

deltaDisplayValue.!description: If this property is set, it is rendered instead of a calculated delta.

showSuggestion.!description:
Deprecated! Since 1.46.0 Use the Group Feed Component instead.
If set to true, a suggest event is fired when the user enters text into the search field. Changing the suggestionItems aggregation in the suggest event listener will display suggestions inside a popup. As of version 1.46, replaced by {@link sap.collaboration.components.feed.Component}.

source.!description: The source of the feed item.

lazyLoading.!description: Enables the Lazy Loading feature that automatically loads more posts as the user scrolls along the timeline axis. This feature works only when the enableScroll property is set to true. See also {@link sap.suite.ui.commons.Timeline#getEnableScroll}.

showToolbar.!description: Defines whether the toolbar is visible.

alignContent.!description: The alignment of the content. If not set, the Left alignment type is used.

filterCriteria.!description: A composite object containing criteria for filtering cards in the Note Taker.

entitySet.!description: The name of the entity set from OData service metadata. The filtering applies to this entity set.

failedText.!description: The message that appears when the control is in the Failed state.

enableModelFilter.!description: Enables filtering directly on the binding level. If set to true, all filters are translated into the filters in the model binding. When the OData model is used, the filtering is performed on the backend side. This option is strongly recommended. If set to false, all entries from the model need to be fetched before they can be filtered on the frontend side. Please be aware that the growingThreshold property determines how many entries can be rendered. Timeline requests all entries from the model before it performs the filtering. Some models may have internal limits for the number of entries that can be used in bindings. Such limits can be set using {@link sap.ui.model.Model#setSizeLimit}.

allowColumnLabels.!description:
If set to true and there is enough space, top labels of the chart are hidden and labels for each column are shown instead.

* @since 1.60.0

allowSuggestions.!description: Defines whether autocomplete suggestions are shown when you type. Available only for desktop devices.

filterValue.!description: Text for the items filter name. This text will be used as the name of the items filter in the filter popover.

maxCharacters.!description: The expand and collapse feature is set by default and uses 300 characters on mobile devices and 500 characters on desktop computers as limits. Based on these values, the text of the timeline post is collapsed once it reaches these character limits. In this case, only the specified number of characters is displayed. By clicking the More link, the entire text can be displayed. Clicking Less collapses the text. The application can set the value according to its needs.

headerType.!description: Defines which header type should be used.

foldedCorners.!description: This property defines the folded corners for the single node control. The following values exist: - true: means folded corner - false/null/undefined: means normal corner

showHeaderBar.!description: Shows the timeline toolbar with search and filter options.

actionsVisible.!description: If set to true, the Actions button appears.

showSearch.!description: Sets the search field visibility on the timeline toolbar.

enableAllInFilterItem.!description:
Deprecated! Since 1.46.0 The filter list now includes a Select All check box, so the All radio button is no longer required. This property is ignored.
Enables to add 'All' at the beginning of the filter list.

renderType.!description:
Determines how the micro process flow should be rendered inside its parent container.
When the width of the parent container does not allow for all nodes in the micro process flow to be displayed, you can wrap it inside the parent container or add scrolling icons.

cancelButtonText.!description: This is the text displayed in the cancelButton. Default value is "Cancel", and it's translated according to the current locale setting. This property will be ignored when running either in iPad or showCancelButton is set to false.

rowSpan.!description:
Deprecated! Since 1.17.1 It is not used any more for the laoyut calculations in UnifiedThingInspector.
Defines the number of rows that the control represents in an external layout.

validationMode.!description:
Defines when the expression is validated.
  • If set to LiveChange, the input is validated as you type.
  • If set to FocusOut, the input is validated, once you press Enter or Tab.

totalLabel.!description: The total label. If specified, it is displayed instead of the total value.

fixedRowHeight.!description: Row height adapts to rendered content. If a fixed height is specified the cells have a maximum height and the overflow will be hidden.

stateText.!description: Description of the state, for example "Status OK".

sidebarWidth.!description: The width of the first panel that contains thing's title, icon, key visual and navigation bar. The default value is "244px".

displayArticleImage.!description: To display article Image or not. If it is true, the article Image will be displayed based on precedence. If it is false, the default image will be displayed.

followActionEnabled.!description: Follow action enabled/disabled. If disabled the action will be invisible.

colorPalette.!description: The color palette for the chart. If this property is set, semantic colors defined in AreaMicroChartItem are ignored. As a result, colors of the palette are assigned to each line. When all the palette colors are used up, assignment of the colors starts again from the beginning of the palette.

wrapItemsInExpression.!description:
Defines whether the expression should be wrapped inside the calculation builder field.
If set to false, the expression is rearranged into a single scrollable row.

showDeltaValue.!description: If set to true, shows the calculated delta value instead of the numeric actual value regardless of the showActualValue setting. This property works in Delta mode only.

iconSrc.!description: Icon to be displayed in the middle of the control.

truncateValueTo.!description: The number of characters to display for the value property.

labelledBy.!description: Identifies one or more elements that label the current element. See the related label and describedBy properties.

children.!description: Defines an array of children of the node.

defaultViewIndex.!description: The index of the default view starting from 0. The view is selected on the initial rendering of the control. If the index is greater than the total quantity of the views, the last view is selected.

imageDescription.!description: Description of a header image that is used in the tooltip.

showThresholds.!description: If set to true, shows the threshold markers.

showSearchField.!description: Indicates if the search field panel is shown.

cardViewAllTrigger.!description: The View All link appears in the Note Taker card when length of a card body text exceeds the specified value. The updated value of this property is not applied to the existing cards.

selectorGroupLabel.!description:
Deprecated! Since 1.32.0 Obsolete property as sap.m.Toolbar is replaced by sap.m.OverflowToolbar.
Custom Label for Selectors Group.

priority.!description: Priority is used to define which label is visible if the state of multiple labels is equal. Assuming there are multiple labels with equal state (e.g. Negative state appears twice), the priority decides which one needs to be selected.

doubleFontSize.!description: If true, the value text will have 2 rem, if false - 1 rem.

scrollingFadeout.!description:
Deprecated! Since 1.54.0 Not Fiori.
If set to Area, the timeline fades into the visible area margin. If set to AreaWithButtons, the timeline fades into the visible area margin and scroll buttons are displayed. If set to None, the fading effect is not applied. This feature works only when the enableScroll property is set to true. See also {@link sap.suite.ui.commons.Timeline#getEnableScroll}.

style.!description: Style of the control (e.g. emphasized, accept)

enabled.!description: Boolean property to enable the control (default is true). Buttons that are disabled have other colors than enabled ones, depending on custom settings.

showIcons.!description: Shows an icon on the timeline axis as an anchor for each entry node. If set to false, all icons are replaced by dots.

blocked.!description:
Deprecated! Since 1.69 The blocked property is deprecated. There is no accessibility support for this property. Blocked controls should not be used inside Controls, which rely on keyboard navigation, e.g. List controls.
Whether the control is currently in blocked state.

iconHovered.!description: A path to the icon representing this view in sap.suite.ui.commons.ViewRepeater view selector when the regular icon is hovered.

attachmentUploadUrl.!description: Sets the upload attachment URL for a new card.

attachmentUrl.!description: Stores the address of the file attached to the card.

showMoreSteps.!description: Step size used to increase the numberOfRows value. This feature is only active if value is greater than 0. This will deactivate the paging feature.

minWidth.!description: The minimal width of the control.

fractionScale.!description: The scaling factor that is displayed after the fraction value.

fraction.!description:
The fraction value that defines the size of the colored sector.
This property must be set to a value that is a fraction of the total value defined for the {@link sap.suite.ui.microchart.HarveyBallMicroChart}.

noDataText.!description: This text is displayed when the control has no data. The default value is loaded from the component resource bundle.

closeButtonVisible.!description: Defines whether the 'Close' button shall be visible.

width.!description: Sets the width of the Timeline.

showViews.!description: Indicates if the view selector panel is shown.

showBottomLabels.!description: If this property is set to false, both bottom labels are hidden.

thumbUp.!description: Sets positive indication for a new note.

indicator.!description: The indicator arrow that shows value deviation.

data.!description:
Deprecated! Since 1.46.0 As of version 1.46, this property was replaced by JSONModel context binding.
Data for the Timeline control.

threshold.!description: Threshold to fetch the next chunk of data. The minimal threshold can be the numberOfRows of the RR.

showActualValueInDeltaMode.!description: If set to true, shows the numeric actual value and possibly hides the delta value, if showDeltaValue is set to true. This property works in Delta mode only and has priority over showDeltaValue.

growing.!description:
Deprecated! Since 1.46.0 Use the growingThreshold property instead, setting it to 0 to disable growing.
If set to true, the timeline displays a limited number of posts with a button to show more. The displayed posts limit can be set using the growingThreshold property. As of version 1.46, replaced by {@link sap.suite.ui.commons.Timeline#getGrowingThreshold}.

showTargetValue.!description: If set to true, shows the numeric target value.

wheelZoomable.!description: Defines if semantic zooming by mouse wheel events on desktop browsers is enabled.

filterTitle.!description: Title for the data filter. When a filter is applied, this title is displayed in the message strip along with the filter name.

headerImage.!description: The image to be displayed as a graphical element within the header. This can be an image or an icon from the icon font.

tag.!description: The user-defined object which is returned back to the user by a node click event.

group.!description:
Deprecated! Since 1.46.0 Use the groupByType property instead.
Groups the timeline posts by year. As of version 1.46, replaced by {@link sap.suite.ui.commons.Timeline#getGroupByType}.

showZoom.!description: Set to true to display zoom icons. Set to false to hide them.

visible.!description: Whether the control should be visible on the screen. If set to false, a placeholder will be rendered to mark the location of the invisible control in the DOM of the current page. The placeholder will be hidden and have zero dimensions (display: none). Also see {@link module:sap/ui/core/InvisibleRenderer InvisibleRenderer}.

attachmentFilename.!description: Stores the name of the file attached to the card.

showInputToolbar.!description:
Defines whether the input toolbar is visible.
The input toolbar contains operators and functions that can be used in the expression.

showTotal.!description: If set to true, the total value is displayed next to the chart. The default setting is true.

wrappingType.!description: Defines the type of text wrapping to be used (hyphenated or normal).

showFilterBar.!description:
Deprecated! Since 1.46.0 Use the showHeaderBar property instead.
Sets the visibility of the filter in the timeline toolbar.
As of version 1.46, replaced by {@link sap.suite.ui.commons.Timeline#getShowHeaderBar}.

scale.!description: The scaling prefix. Financial characters can be used for currencies and counters. The SI prefixes can be used for units.

valueStatus.!description: The status color of the value. Depending on the status the tile is displayed in different colors.

highlightText.!description: Defines the semantics of the {@link sap.m.ListItemBase#setHighlight highlight} property for accessibility purposes.

textDirection.!description: This property specifies the element's text directionality with enumerated options. By default, the control inherits text direction from the DOM.

highlight.!description: Defines the highlight state of the list items. Valid values for the highlight property are values of the enumerations {@link sap.ui.core.MessageType} or {@link sap.ui.core.IndicationColor}. Accessibility support is provided through the associated {@link sap.m.ListItemBase#setHighlightText highlightText} property. If the highlight property is set to a value of {@link sap.ui.core.MessageType}, the highlightText property does not need to be set because a default text is used. However, the default text can be overridden by setting the highlightText property. In all other cases the highlightText property must be set.

minValue.!description: The minimum scale value for the chart used to define the value range of the scale for comparing different values.

showBubbles.!description: Property to show or hide bubbles. Default is true.

quantity.!description: Displays a label with the number of items in the right part of the control.

userNameClickable.!description: Makes the user name clickable. Clicking the name fires a userNameClicked event.

groupByType.!description: Groups the timeline posts by a time period, including year, quarter, month, week, and day. If set to None, no grouping is applied. If you specify a custom grouping function using the {@link sap.suite.ui.commons.Timeline#setCustomGrouping} method, this function overrides the groupByType property settings.

totalUnits.!description: Number of units that are displayed by ticks. The PageUp and PageDown keys navigate according to these units.

ariaLabel.!description: ARIA label for this control to be used by screen reader software.

sizeBehavior.!description: If set to TileSizeBehavior.Small, the tile size is the same as it would be on a small-screened phone (374px wide and lower), regardless of the screen size of the actual device being used. If set to TileSizeBehavior.Responsive, the tile size adapts to the size of the screen.

animateTextChange.!description: If set to true, changing of the value is animated.

autoAdjustHeight.!description: Determine whether to stretch the chart height to the maximum possible height of ChartContainer's parent container. As a prerequisite, the parent container needs to have a fixed value height or be able to determine height from its parent.

responsive.!description: This parameter indicates whether the content is shown in rows or tiles. If false, the content is shown in rows just like in core sap.ui.commons.RowRepeater. If true, the content is shown in tiles (similar to sap.ui.ux3.DataSet control) that have minimal width defined by the "itemMinWidth" property. The number of columns depends on the parent control's width. If you resize the control, the number of columns may change respectively so that the content tiles can fill the entire space of a row.

backgroundDesign.!description: Specifies the background color of the content. The visualization of the different options depends on the used theme.

sap.suite.ui.commons.imageeditor.ImageEd.!description:
This control acts as a wrapper around the {@link sap.suite.ui.commons.imageeditor.ImageEditor} control. It provides additional image editing capabilities for the convenience of your users.

Toolbar Customization

There are two ways to customize the toolbar, but they cannot be used together:
  • Use enabledButtons property to select the order and visibility of the buttons provided by the ImageEditorContainer control. You can use the customToolbarControls aggregation to add custom controls that will be rendered in the toolbar.
  • Use the {@link #getToolbar} method together with the {@link #getToolbarIds} method to customize the toolbar as you need.
    The changes made to the toolbar will be kept unless some of the methods from previous approach are used. The previous approach involves rerendering of the toolbar, which causes all changes to be lost. Note: If you use this approach, make sure that you make your changes to the mobile toolbars as well, so that your application can be used on mobile devices.
    There are three mobile toolbars available:
    • The header toolbar that can be customized using the method {@link #getMobileHeaderToolbar} and is intended for custom buttons.
    • The zoom toolbar contains zoom functionality that can be customized using the methods {@link #getMobileZoomToolbar} and {@link #getMobileZoomToolbarIds}.
    • The footer toolbar that usually includes the ImageEditorContainer buttons and can be customized using the methods {@link #getMobileFooterToolbar} and {@link #getMobileFooterToolbarIds}.

sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.layout.!constructorDescription:
Constructor for a new ForceBasedLayout. Accepts an object literal mSettings that defines initial property values, aggregated and associated objects as well as event handlers. See {@link sap.ui.base.ManagedObject#constructor} for a general description of the syntax of the settings object.

The supported settings are:

  • Properties
    • {@link #getAlpha alpha} : float (default: 0.3)
    • {@link #getCharge charge} : float (default: -30)
    • {@link #getFriction friction} : float (default: 0.9)
    • {@link #getMaximumDuration maximumDuration} : int (default: 1000)
In addition, all settings applicable to the base type {@link sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.layout.LayoutAlgorithm#constructor sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.layout.LayoutAlgorithm} can be used as well.
sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.layout.!helpDescription: This algorithm uses D3.force algorithm to layout the graph. It's good if the graph is too complicated and LayeredLayout is not sufficient.

parameters.fCharge: type: float, description: New value for property charge

isLayered.!description: Specifies if this layouting algorithm distributes nodes into layers. Parent graph may change behaviour based on this option.

setMaximumDuration.!description: Sets a new value for property {@link #getMaximumDuration maximumDuration}. Specifies the maximal time in miliseconds the algorithm is allowed to run. When called with a value of null or undefined, the default value of the property will be restored. Default value is 1000.

parameters.iMaximumDuration: type: int, description: New value for property maximumDuration

setFriction.!description: Sets a new value for property {@link #getFriction friction}. Value in [0,1] range. See: {@link https://github.com/d3/d3-3.x-api-reference/blob/master/Force-Layout.md#friction} When called with a value of null or undefined, the default value of the property will be restored. Default value is 0.9.

setFullAnimationDuration.!description:
Deprecated! Since 1.54.1 All animations are now limited to 250 ms.
Sets a new value for property {@link #getFullAnimationDuration fullAnimationDuration}. Specifies the duration, in milliseconds, of the animation that would fill an empty shape to the full. The actual time it takes to change the shape's filling is proportional to the difference between the initial and the target status indicator's value. For example, a change from 20 percent to 70 percent takes only half of the time specified in the fullAnimationDuration property. If this property is set to 0, changes are applied instantly without any animation. When called with a value of null or undefined, the default value of the property will be restored. Default value is 0.

Gets current value of property {@link #getFullAnimationDuration fullAnimationDuration}. Specifies the duration, in milliseconds, of the animation that would fill an empty shape to the full. The actual time it takes to change the shape's filling is proportional to the difference between the initial and the target status indicator's value. For example, a change from 20 percent to 70 percent takes only half of the time specified in the fullAnimationDuration property. If this property is set to 0, changes are applied instantly without any animation. Default value is 0.

getFillingAngle.!description:
Gets current value of property {@link #getFillingAngle fillingAngle}. Defines the angle at which the shape is filled. This property overrides the fillingDirection property.
Accepted values include 0 through 360 degrees.
For example, if you set the filling angle to 45, the shape will be filled diagonally from the lower right part of the shape to its upper left part.
This property can be used only when {@link sap.suite.ui.commons.statusindicator.FillingType} is set to Linear. Default value is undefined.

setHorizontalAlignment.!description: Sets a new value for property {@link #getHorizontalAlignment horizontalAlignment}. Defines the horizontal alignment of the shape within its parent container. When called with a value of null or undefined, the default value of the property will be restored. Default value is Middle.

maxTime.!description: Maximum time in milliseconds the layouting process will run for.

maxIterations.!description: Maximum number of iterations (or cooldown steps) the layouting process will go through.

maximumDuration.!description: Specifies the maximal time in miliseconds the algorithm is allowed to run.

initialTemperature.!description: Initial 'temperature' of the system, that controls the step width of the nodes' movements and that decreases, or 'cools down', after each iteration.

coolDownStep.!description: Specifies how much the 'temperature' decreases after every iteration.

nodePlacement.!description: A node placement strategy to use (see {@link sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.NodePlacement}).

optimalDistanceConstant.!description: The "C" constant from the optimal distance equation used in the Fruchterman-Reingold Algorithm. See {@link https://www.researchgate.net/publication/309193795_Force-Directed_Graph_Drawing_Algorithm}

staticNodes.!description: List of keys of nodes that should ignore cooldown iterations and keep their original positions (x and y coordinates) in the graph.

nodeSpacing.!description: Define a minimal distance on nodes the algorithm will try to keep. The default value is 55. Note that values below 50 are incompatible with presence of groups due to insufficient space for group title bars and space between nodes and their groups' borders.

mergeEdges.!description: Determines if all lines should lead to the same place in the node, or if each line should point to a different place.

getMetadata.!description: Returns a metadata object for class sap.suite.ui.commons.statusindicator.FillingOption.

getWeight.!description:
Gets current value of property {@link #getWeight weight}. Weight of the fillable shape, relative to other fillable shapes included in this custom shape. This property allows you to distribute the status indicator's value between distinct SVG shapes included in the custom shape. For example, for four SVG shapes with weights 1, 2, 3, and 4 (total weight 10), the status indicator's value is distributed in the following way:
  • If the status indicator's value is below 10% (1 out of 10), the first SVG shape (weight 1) is partially filled, depending on the percentage value. For example, if the percentage value of the status indicator is 5, the first SVG shape appears half-full. The rest of the SVG shapes appear empty.
  • If the status indicator's value is at least 10% but below 30%, the first SVG shape (weight 1) is filled, and the second shape (weight 2) is filled only partially, depending on the percentage value. The rest of the SVG shapes in this custom shape appear empty.
  • If the status indicator's value is at least 30% but below 60%, the first two SVG shapes (weight 1 and 2) are filled, and the third SVG shape (weight 3) is filled only partially. The fourth SVG shape (weight 4) appears empty.
  • If the status indicator's value is at least 60% but below 100%, the first three SVG shapes (weight 1, 2, and 3) are filled, but the fourth SVG shape is filled only partially, depending on the percentage value.
  • If the status indicator's value is 100, all four SVG shapes appear filled.
Default value is 1.

setWeight.!description:
Sets a new value for property {@link #getWeight weight}. Weight of the fillable shape, relative to other fillable shapes included in this custom shape. This property allows you to distribute the status indicator's value between distinct SVG shapes included in the custom shape. For example, for four SVG shapes with weights 1, 2, 3, and 4 (total weight 10), the status indicator's value is distributed in the following way:
  • If the status indicator's value is below 10% (1 out of 10), the first SVG shape (weight 1) is partially filled, depending on the percentage value. For example, if the percentage value of the status indicator is 5, the first SVG shape appears half-full. The rest of the SVG shapes appear empty.
  • If the status indicator's value is at least 10% but below 30%, the first SVG shape (weight 1) is filled, and the second shape (weight 2) is filled only partially, depending on the percentage value. The rest of the SVG shapes in this custom shape appear empty.
  • If the status indicator's value is at least 30% but below 60%, the first two SVG shapes (weight 1 and 2) are filled, and the third SVG shape (weight 3) is filled only partially. The fourth SVG shape (weight 4) appears empty.
  • If the status indicator's value is at least 60% but below 100%, the first three SVG shapes (weight 1, 2, and 3) are filled, but the fourth SVG shape is filled only partially, depending on the percentage value.
  • If the status indicator's value is 100, all four SVG shapes appear filled.
When called with a value of null or undefined, the default value of the property will be restored. Default value is 1.

parameters.iWeight: type: int, description: New value for property weight

Deprecated! Since 1.32 Type is deprecated because of no usages. There will be no replacement.
Sets a new value for property {@link #getType type}. Type of the connection. When called with a value of null or undefined, the default value of the property will be restored. Default value is Normal.

parameters.sType: type: sap.suite.ui.commons.ProcessFlowConnectionType, description: New value for property type

getDrawData.!description:
Gets current value of property {@link #getDrawData drawData}.

This is an array of the following attributes for one element: 1. flowLine (string) - A connection definition where the line should be drawn. A string which defines a course of a flow line. A flow line is a connection between nodes in a process flow control. The string can contain the following characters: - "r" for right, - "t" for top, - "l" for left, - "b" for bottom. 2. targetNodeState (ProcessFlowNodeState) - A copy of the target node status. If the target node is created, the line is solid. If the target node is planned, the line is dashed. 3. displayState (ProcessFlowDisplayState) - Display state of the node. This property defines if the node is displayed regularly, highlighted, or dimmed in combination with a selected visual style of the control. 4. hasArrow (boolean) - Indicates if the line has an arrow on the right end.

sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.layout.!description: This algorithm uses the deterministic variant of the force-directed layout algorithm {@link sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.layout.ForceBasedLayout} to arrange the nodes included in the network graph. It can be useful for complex graphs, where {@link sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.layout.LayeredLayout} is not sufficient.

getCoolDownStep.!description: Gets current value of property {@link #getCoolDownStep coolDownStep}. Specifies how much the 'temperature' decreases after every iteration. Default value is 1.

setOptimalDistanceConstant.!description: Sets a new value for property {@link #getOptimalDistanceConstant optimalDistanceConstant}. The "C" constant from the optimal distance equation used in the Fruchterman-Reingold Algorithm. See {@link https://www.researchgate.net/publication/309193795_Force-Directed_Graph_Drawing_Algorithm} When called with a value of null or undefined, the default value of the property will be restored. Default value is 0.2.

sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.layout.!constructorDescription:
Constructor for a new ForceDirectedLayout. Accepts an object literal mSettings that defines initial property values, aggregated and associated objects as well as event handlers. See {@link sap.ui.base.ManagedObject#constructor} for a general description of the syntax of the settings object.

The supported settings are:

  • Properties
    • {@link #getOptimalDistanceConstant optimalDistanceConstant} : float (default: 0.2)
    • {@link #getMaxIterations maxIterations} : int (default: 200)
    • {@link #getMaxTime maxTime} : int (default: 2000)
    • {@link #getInitialTemperature initialTemperature} : float (default: 200)
    • {@link #getCoolDownStep coolDownStep} : float (default: 1)
    • {@link #getStaticNodes staticNodes} : string[] (default: [])
In addition, all settings applicable to the base type {@link sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.layout.LayoutAlgorithm#constructor sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.layout.LayoutAlgorithm} can be used as well.

getInitialTemperature.!description: Gets current value of property {@link #getInitialTemperature initialTemperature}. Initial 'temperature' of the system, that controls the step width of the nodes' movements and that decreases, or 'cools down', after each iteration. Default value is 200.

getMaxIterations.!description: Gets current value of property {@link #getMaxIterations maxIterations}. Maximum number of iterations (or cooldown steps) the layouting process will go through. Default value is 200.

setStaticNodes.!description: Sets a new value for property {@link #getStaticNodes staticNodes}. List of keys of nodes that should ignore cooldown iterations and keep their original positions (x and y coordinates) in the graph. When called with a value of null or undefined, the default value of the property will be restored. Default value is [].

parameters.sStaticNodes: type: string[], description: New value for property staticNodes

sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.layout.!helpDescription: This algorithm uses the deterministic variant of the force-directed layout algorithm {@link sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.layout.ForceBasedLayout} to arrange the nodes included in the network graph. It can be useful for complex graphs, where {@link sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.layout.LayeredLayout} is not sufficient.

setMaxIterations.!description: Sets a new value for property {@link #getMaxIterations maxIterations}. Maximum number of iterations (or cooldown steps) the layouting process will go through. When called with a value of null or undefined, the default value of the property will be restored. Default value is 200.

parameters.iMaxIterations: type: int, description: New value for property maxIterations

isLayered.!description: Specifies if this layout algorithm distributes nodes into layers. The parent graph may affect the behaviour based on this option.

The container that provides a horizontal layout. It provides a horizontal scroll on the tablet and phone. On the desktop, it provides scroll left and scroll right buttons. This control supports keyboard navigation. You can use left and right arrow keys to navigate through the inner content. getDateTime.!description:
Gets current value of property {@link #getDateTime dateTime}. Date and time value of the timeline post. This value must be in one of the following formats:
  • A valid instance of the Date object.
  • An integer representing Unix time (also known as POSIX or Epoch time) in milliseconds.
  • A string with an integer representing Unix time in milliseconds.
  • A string that contains Date([number]), where [number] represents Unix time in milliseconds.
If this property has any other format, the timeline will try to parse it using Date.parse. It is not recommended to use this functionality, as different web browsers implement this function differently, which may lead to unpredictable behavior.

sap.suite.ui.commons.TimelineItem.!constructorDescription:
Constructor for a new TimelineItem. Accepts an object literal mSettings that defines initial property values, aggregated and associated objects as well as event handlers. See {@link sap.ui.base.ManagedObject#constructor} for a general description of the syntax of the settings object.

The supported settings are:

  • Properties
    • {@link #getDateTime dateTime} : any
    • {@link #getFilterValue filterValue} : string
    • {@link #getIcon icon} : string
    • {@link #getIconTooltip iconTooltip} : string
    • {@link #getUseIconTooltip useIconTooltip} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getMaxCharacters maxCharacters} : int
    • {@link #getReplyCount replyCount} : int
    • {@link #getStatus status} : string
    • {@link #getTitle title} : string
    • {@link #getText text} : string
    • {@link #getUserName userName} : string
    • {@link #getUserNameClickable userNameClickable} : boolean (default: false)
    • {@link #getUserPicture userPicture} : sap.ui.core.URI
  • Aggregations
    • {@link #getCustomAction customAction} : sap.ui.core.CustomData[]
    • {@link #getCustomReply customReply} : sap.ui.core.Control
    • {@link #getEmbeddedControl embeddedControl} : sap.ui.core.Control (default)
    • {@link #getReplyList replyList} : sap.m.List
    • {@link #getSuggestionItems suggestionItems} : sap.m.StandardListItem[]
  • Events
    • {@link #event:userNameClicked userNameClicked} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:replyPost replyPost} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:replyListOpen replyListOpen} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:customActionClicked customActionClicked} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:suggest suggest} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:suggestionItemSelected suggestionItemSelected} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
In addition, all settings applicable to the base type {@link sap.ui.core.Control#constructor sap.ui.core.Control} can be used as well.

parameters.oEmbeddedControl: type: sap.ui.core.Control, description: The embeddedControl to set

getIcon.!description:
Gets current value of property {@link #getIcon icon}.

Icon on the timeline axis that corresponds to the point in time when the entry was posted. Posts can be displayed in chronological or reverse chronological order.

setDateTime.!description:
Sets a new value for property {@link #getDateTime dateTime}. Date and time value of the timeline post. This value must be in one of the following formats:
  • A valid instance of the Date object.
  • An integer representing Unix time (also known as POSIX or Epoch time) in milliseconds.
  • A string with an integer representing Unix time in milliseconds.
  • A string that contains Date([number]), where [number] represents Unix time in milliseconds.
If this property has any other format, the timeline will try to parse it using Date.parse. It is not recommended to use this functionality, as different web browsers implement this function differently, which may lead to unpredictable behavior. When called with a value of null or undefined, the default value of the property will be restored.

parameters.oDateTime: type: any, description: New value for property dateTime

sap.suite.ui.commons.ChartContainer.!constructorDescription:
Constructor for a new ChartContainer. Accepts an object literal mSettings that defines initial property values, aggregated and associated objects as well as event handlers. See {@link sap.ui.base.ManagedObject#constructor} for a general description of the syntax of the settings object.

The supported settings are:

  • Properties
    • {@link #getShowPersonalization showPersonalization} : boolean (default: false)
    • {@link #getShowFullScreen showFullScreen} : boolean (default: false)
    • {@link #getFullScreen fullScreen} : boolean (default: false)
    • {@link #getShowLegend showLegend} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getTitle title} : string (default: )
    • {@link #getSelectorGroupLabel selectorGroupLabel} : string
    • {@link #getAutoAdjustHeight autoAdjustHeight} : boolean (default: false)
    • {@link #getShowZoom showZoom} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getShowLegendButton showLegendButton} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getShowSelectionDetails showSelectionDetails} : boolean (default: false)
    • {@link #getWrapLabels wrapLabels} : boolean (default: false)
    • {@link #getEnableScroll enableScroll} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getWidth width} : sap.ui.core.CSSSize (default: 100%)
  • Aggregations
    • {@link #getDimensionSelectors dimensionSelectors} : sap.ui.core.Control[]
    • {@link #getContent content} : sap.suite.ui.commons.ChartContainerContent[] (default)
    • {@link #getToolbar toolbar} : sap.m.OverflowToolbar

sap.suite.ui.commons.ProcessFlowNode.!constructorDescription:
Constructor for a new ProcessFlowNode. Accepts an object literal mSettings that defines initial property values, aggregated and associated objects as well as event handlers. See {@link sap.ui.base.ManagedObject#constructor} for a general description of the syntax of the settings object.

The supported settings are:

  • Properties
    • {@link #getTitle title} : string
    • {@link #getIsTitleClickable isTitleClickable} : boolean (default: false)
    • {@link #getLaneId laneId} : string
    • {@link #getNodeId nodeId} : string
    • {@link #getState state} : sap.suite.ui.commons.ProcessFlowNodeState (default: Neutral)
    • {@link #getType type} : sap.suite.ui.commons.ProcessFlowNodeType (default: Single)
    • {@link #getChildren children} : any[]
    • {@link #getTitleAbbreviation titleAbbreviation} : string
    • {@link #getStateText stateText} : string
    • {@link #getTexts texts} : string[]
    • {@link #getHighlighted highlighted} : boolean (default: false)
    • {@link #getFocused focused} : boolean (default: false)
    • {@link #getTag tag} : object
    • {@link #getSelected selected} : boolean (default: false)
  • Aggregations
    • {@link #getZoomLevelOneContent zoomLevelOneContent} : sap.ui.core.Control
    • {@link #getZoomLevelTwoContent zoomLevelTwoContent} : sap.ui.core.Control
    • {@link #getZoomLevelThreeContent zoomLevelThreeContent} : sap.ui.core.Control
    • {@link #getZoomLevelFourContent zoomLevelFourContent} : sap.ui.core.Control
    • {@link #getAriaProperties ariaProperties} : sap.suite.ui.commons.AriaProperties
  • Associations
    • {@link #getParents parents} : (sap.ui.core.ID | sap.suite.ui.commons.ProcessFlowNode)[]
  • Events
    • {@link #event:titlePress titlePress} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:press press} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
In addition, all settings applicable to the base type {@link sap.ui.core.Control#constructor sap.ui.core.Control} can be used as well.

getGroup.!description:
Gets current value of property {@link #getGroup group}.

Key of the group where this node is included.

getDescriptionLineSize.!description: Gets current value of property {@link #getDescriptionLineSize descriptionLineSize}. Determines the maximum number of lines allowed to be displayed in the node's description. If you want to hide the description, set this property to -1 (default). To display an unlimited number of lines, set this property to 0. This property does not affect the description that appears in the tooltip, which is always fully rendered. Default value is -1.

getActionLinks.!description:
Gets content of aggregation {@link #getActionLinks actionLinks}.

A list of links to be shown in the links area. A link may point to any UI5 control. It's up to the caller to set up all necessary callback functions.

getContent.!description:
Gets content of aggregation {@link #getContent content}.

Custom content rendered with the node. Available only for rectangular nodes with HTML rendering type. When this aggregation is used, the description and attributes of {@link sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.ElementBase} are ignored.

setCollapsed.!description: Sets a new value for property {@link #getCollapsed collapsed}. Defines if the subtree of this node is collapsed. By default, it is expanded. When called with a value of null or undefined, the default value of the property will be restored. Default value is false.

parameters.bCollapsed: type: boolean, description: New value for property collapsed

getShape.!description: Gets current value of property {@link #getShape shape}. Shape of the node. The shape is round by default. To create a rectangular node, set this property to Box. Default value is Circle.

getChildLines.!description: Returns all lines connected to the child nodes.

getShowExpandButton.!description: Gets current value of property {@link #getShowExpandButton showExpandButton}. Determines if the expand button is visible. Default value is true.

renderText.!description: Renders the text of the node as SVG. Either text or lines of text must be passed to this method as an argument.

parameters.mArguments: type: Object, description: Arguments passed to the method

sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.Node.!constructorDescription:
Constructor for a new Node. Accepts an object literal mSettings that defines initial property values, aggregated and associated objects as well as event handlers. See {@link sap.ui.base.ManagedObject#constructor} for a general description of the syntax of the settings object.

The supported settings are:

  • Properties
    • {@link #getHeaderCheckBoxState headerCheckBoxState} : sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.HeaderCheckboxState (default: Hidden)
    • {@link #getCollapsed collapsed} : boolean (default: false)
    • {@link #getSelected selected} : boolean (default: false)
    • {@link #getGroup group} : string
    • {@link #getKey key} : string
    • {@link #getShape shape} : sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.NodeShape (default: Circle)
    • {@link #getIcon icon} : string
    • {@link #getStatusIcon statusIcon} : string
    • {@link #getWidth width} : int (default: undefined)
    • {@link #getHeight height} : int (default: undefined)
    • {@link #getMaxWidth maxWidth} : int (default: undefined)
    • {@link #getX x} : float (default: 0)
    • {@link #getY y} : float (default: 0)
    • {@link #getShowExpandButton showExpandButton} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getShowActionLinksButton showActionLinksButton} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getShowDetailButton showDetailButton} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getTitleLineSize titleLineSize} : int (default: 1)
    • {@link #getDescriptionLineSize descriptionLineSize} : int (default: -1)
    • {@link #getIconSize iconSize} : int (default: undefined)
    • {@link #getCoreNodeSize coreNodeSize} : int (default: 0)
    • {@link #getVisible visible} : boolean (default: true)
  • Aggregations
    • {@link #getActionLinks actionLinks} : sap.ui.core.Control[]
    • {@link #getActionButtons actionButtons} : sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.ActionButton[]
    • {@link #getImage image} : sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.NodeImage
    • {@link #getContent content} : sap.ui.core.Control
  • Events
    • {@link #event:headerCheckBoxPress headerCheckBoxPress} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:press press} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:hover hover} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:collapseExpand collapseExpand} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
In addition, all settings applicable to the base type {@link sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.ElementBase#constructor sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.ElementBase} can be used as well.

Deprecated! Since 1.69 The blocked property is deprecated. There is no accessibility support for this property. Blocked controls should not be used inside Controls, which rely on keyboard navigation, e.g. List controls.
Whether the control is currently in blocked state.

busyIndicatorDelay.!description: The delay in milliseconds, after which the busy indicator will show up for this control.

busy.!description: Whether the control is currently in busy state.

fieldGroupIds.!description: The IDs of a logical field group that this control belongs to. All fields in a logical field group should share the same fieldGroupId. Once a logical field group is left, the validateFieldGroup event is fired. For backward compatibility with older releases, field group IDs are syntactically not limited, but it is suggested to use only valid {@link sap.ui.core.ID}s. See {@link #attachValidateFieldGroup} or consult the {@link topic:5b0775397e394b1fb973fa207554003e Field Group} documentation.

openingDebit.!description: Opening debit balance of the T account.

state.!description:
State of the panel that defines how T accounts are displayed.
By default, the T accounts included in the panel are displayed as T shapes with debit and credit entries on either side of the T.

group.!description:
Group where this debit or credit entry belongs.
Entries that share the same group are highlighted when the user clicks or taps one of such entries.

displayLabel.!description:
Defines whether the label should be displayed.
This property can be overridden by the {@link sap.suite.ui.commons.TAccountPanel} settings.

openingCredit.!description: Opening credit balance of the T account.

visible.!description: Whether the control should be visible on the screen. If set to false, a placeholder will be rendered to mark the location of the invisible control in the DOM of the current page. The placeholder will be hidden and have zero dimensions (display: none). Also see {@link module:sap/ui/core/InvisibleRenderer InvisibleRenderer}.

label.!description:
Label of the property.
Can be hidden or displayed using the displayLabel property.

opening.!description: Mode with opening and closing balance of the T account.

sap.suite.ui.commons.imageeditor.ImageEd.!constructorDescription:
Constructor for a new ImageEditor. Accepts an object literal mSettings that defines initial property values, aggregated and associated objects as well as event handlers. See {@link sap.ui.base.ManagedObject#constructor} for a general description of the syntax of the settings object.

The supported settings are:

  • Properties
    • {@link #getSrc src} : any (default: )
    • {@link #getCustomShapeSrc customShapeSrc} : any (default: )
    • {@link #getMode mode} : sap.suite.ui.commons.ImageEditorMode (default: Default)
    • {@link #getKeepCropAspectRatio keepCropAspectRatio} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getKeepResizeAspectRatio keepResizeAspectRatio} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getScaleCropArea scaleCropArea} : boolean (default: false)
  • Events
    • {@link #event:loaded loaded} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:error error} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:customShapeLoaded customShapeLoaded} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:customShapeError customShapeError} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:sizeChanged sizeChanged} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:cropAreaChanged cropAreaChanged} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:zoomChanged zoomChanged} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:historyChanged historyChanged} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
In addition, all settings applicable to the base type {@link sap.ui.core.Control#constructor sap.ui.core.Control} can be used as well.

This method works only when the {@link sap.suite.ui.commons.ImageEditorMode} is set to CropRectangle or CropEllipse.

parameters.bPreview: type: boolean, description: Indicates whether to show this action in preview only (true) or record it in action history as well (false)

setMode.!description:
Sets a new value for property {@link #getMode mode}. Image editor mode.
Four modes are available: resize mode, crop to rectangle mode, crop to circle mode, and display image mode (default).
The default mode displays the image to be edited. When called with a value of null or undefined, the default value of the property will be restored. Default value is Default.

parameters.sMode: type: sap.suite.ui.commons.ImageEditorMode, description: New value for property mode

parameters.bPreview: type: boolean, description: Indicates whether to show this action in preview only (true) or record it in action history as well (false)

zoom.!description: Zooms in or out to the specified zoom level.

parameters.fZoom: type: float, description: Level of zoom
parameters.mParameters: type: object, description: Map which contains following parameters properties:

rectangleCrop.!description: Crops the image to a new rectangle-shaped image based on the specified pixel parameters.
rectangleCrop.!type: fn(iX: Number, iY: Number, iWidth: Number, iHeight: Number, bPreview: Boolean)

parameters.iY: type: int, description: Y coordinate of the top left corner of the crop area
parameters.bPreview: type: boolean, description: Indicates whether to show this action in preview only (true) or record it in action history as well (false)
parameters.iWidth: type: int, description: Width of the crop area
parameters.iHeight: type: int, description: Height of the crop area
parameters.iX: type: int, description: X coordinate of the top left corner of the crop area

setWidth.!description:
Sets the width of the image in pixels.
If the property keepResizeAspectRatio is set to true, changes the current image height as well (even in preview state).

parameters.bPreview: type: boolean, description: Indicates whether to show this action in preview only (true) or record it in action history as well (false)
parameters.iWidth: type: int, description: New width of the image in pixels

getKeepCropAspectRatio.!description: Gets current value of property {@link #getKeepCropAspectRatio keepCropAspectRatio}. Defines whether aspect ratio should be kept when the crop area is expanded or shrunk in the CropRectangle or CropEllipse modes ({@link sap.suite.ui.commons.ImageEditorMode}). Default value is true.

sepia.!description: Applies the sepia filter to the image.

parameters.bPreview: type: boolean, description: Indicates whether to show this action in preview only (true) or record it in action history as well (false)
parameters.iValue: type: int, description: Filter strength. Applicable range of values is from 0 to 100

brightness.!description: Applies the brightness filter to the image.

parameters.bPreview: type: boolean, description: Indicates whether to show this action in preview only (true) or record it in action history as well (false)
parameters.iValue: type: int, description: Filter strength. Applicable range of values is from 0 to 500

fireError.!description: Fires event {@link #event:error error} to attached listeners.

parameters.mParameters: type: object, description: Parameters to pass along with the event

setCropAreaBySize.!description:
Resizes the crop area to the specified height and width.
The size is expected to be in pixel values corresponding to the actual size of the image.
Crop area is automatically constrained, so that it doesn't overflow the edges of the image.

parameters.iWidth: type: int, description: Width of the cropping area
parameters.iHeight: type: int, description: Height of the cropping area

setScaleCropArea.!description:
Sets a new value for property {@link #getScaleCropArea scaleCropArea}. Defines the behavior of the crop area when zooming in or out.
If set to true, the crop area is scaled up or down when the zoom level is changed.
If set to false, the crop area remains unchanged and keeps its size. When called with a value of null or undefined, the default value of the property will be restored. Default value is false.

parameters.bScaleCropArea: type: boolean, description: New value for property scaleCropArea

applyPreview.!description: Saves current preview to action history, if there is any.

parameters.fnFunction: type: function, description: The function to be called, when the event occurs

parameters.fQuality: type: float, description: Quality of the returned image, ranging from 0 to 1. 0 means highly compressed image, 1 means uncompressed image. When no value is provided, canvas default compression level is used.
